{{version030}}
{{flavour|Sings a powerfully haunting song; in addition to making nearby victims unwilling to move away from the singer, it calls forth drowned souls from any nearby bodies of deep water.}}

'''Avatar Song''' is a monster-only spell that attempts to [[mesmerise]] the player. Mesmerise prevents the player from intentionally moving away from the singer, and prevents [[berserk]]. In addition, Avatar Song gradually pulls the target towards the caster, and creates [[drowned soul]]s that inflict [[drowning]] damage. The mesmerise effect can be blocked by [[willpower]], but requires no line of fire.

If you are immune to mesmerise (e.g. via [[clarity]]) or beat mesmerise through willpower, Avatar Song will still create drowned souls. Disabling the caster (e.g. with [[confusion]]) ends the effect entirely.

{{monsters with spell}}

==History==
Prior to [[0.20]], you could break out of the spell by making a sufficiently loud noise (such as from a [[scroll of noise]]).

